The paper deals with the performance analysis of spatially coupled low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network coding (cs.NT). The refined scaling law proposed in the paper involves the analysis of the coupling strength and the degree distribution of the code, which are also relevant to coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the simulation results and the comparison with previous works, which involves data analysis and statistics (cs.DS) and performance evaluation (cs.SI).
